this is something in
principle we can never know.

00:42:02.100 --> 00:42:03.510
We'll have to see.

00:42:03.510 --> 00:42:05.780
- What do you think will be
the implications of this,

00:42:05.780 --> 00:42:07.430
if you can come up with an answer?

00:42:07.430 --> 00:42:10.590
In other words, does it have an impact

00:42:10.590 --> 00:42:11.870
on the treatment of disease?

00:42:11.870 --> 00:42:15.900
Does it have an impact on who we are,

00:42:15.900 --> 00:42:16.977
and understanding our
place in the universe?

00:42:16.977 --> 00:42:18.190
- Yes, yes, yes.

00:42:18.190 --> 00:42:19.640
Well, certainly there's no question

00:42:19.640 --> 00:42:20.520
it'll have an impact on disease,

00:42:20.520 --> 00:42:23.930
and understanding things
like autism, schizophrenia.

00:42:23.930 --> 00:42:27.660
But more even longer term,

00:42:27.660 --> 00:42:29.150
whatever the understanding will be

00:42:29.150 --> 00:42:32.240
you see, we grew up with
a picture in our history,

00:42:32.240 --> 00:42:35.260
in our culture, that we grew very fond of.

00:42:35.260 --> 00:42:38.300
And it remains to be seen
to what extent this picture

00:42:38.300 --> 00:42:40.510
you know of people independent
actor having free will,

00:42:40.510 --> 00:42:43.230
and a soul, and all of that
corresponds to actual reality.

00:42:43.230 --> 00:42:46.893
And so we have to see how it pans out.

00:42:48.100 --> 00:42:49.113
Do we really know what we are

00:42:49.113 --> 00:42:51.650
and what's our place in the
universe, and are we unique?

00:42:51.650 --> 00:42:53.150
Is consciousness unique to us?

00:42:54.402 --> 00:42:55.390
What about animals?

00:42:55.390 --> 00:42:57.410
Right now we treat animals beastly, right?

00:42:57.410 --> 00:42:59.835
If you look at the way
the animals are raised

00:42:59.835 --> 00:43:03.340
and kept under horrible
conditions for us to eat 'em,

00:43:03.340 --> 00:43:04.940
is that really justifiable, really?

00:43:04.940 --> 00:43:06.716
I don't think it is.

00:43:06.716 --> 00:43:08.180
And so once we realize,

00:43:08.180 --> 00:43:11.460
once we extend this magic
circle of consciousness,

00:43:11.460 --> 00:43:13.260
once we're really compassionate
about other creatures

00:43:13.260 --> 00:43:14.450
that can actually suffer,

00:43:14.450 --> 00:43:16.300
and have a true understanding of that,

00:43:16.300 --> 00:43:19.270
and at the same time
realize that certain people

00:43:19.270 --> 00:43:22.480
cannot suffer anymore,
that a patient in PVS,

00:43:22.480 --> 00:43:25.500
in persistent vegetative
syndrome like Terri Schiavo,

00:43:25.500 --> 00:43:27.410
as far as we can tell from
the best medical evidence,

00:43:27.410 --> 00:43:30.250
there isn't anything to
suffer anymore, right.

00:43:30.250 --> 00:43:32.450
The person isn't dead because
the body's still alive,

00:43:32.450 --> 00:43:34.420
but there's no consciousness whatsoever.

00:43:34.420 --> 00:43:36.060
So, you could argue a person

00:43:36.060 --> 00:43:38.090
like that should be extended less.

00:43:38.090 --> 00:43:40.360
It's sort of on the
level of consciousness,

00:43:40.360 --> 00:43:44.060
much, much less conscious
than any of our cats and dogs,

00:43:44.060 --> 00:43:48.780
and pigs and cattle and veal
that we treat horribly, right.

00:43:48.780 --> 00:43:52.690
So, all of this understanding will surely

00:43:52.690 --> 00:43:55.290
or is gonna impact the way
we deal, we treat each other

00:43:55.290 --> 00:43:57.650
and we treat the other
creatures in the world.

00:43:57.650 --> 00:43:59.050
And then of course, the question

00:43:59.050 --> 00:44:01.800
should we create other conscious
entities, like computers?

00:44:01.800 --> 00:44:02.633
Is it a good thing?

00:44:02.633 --> 00:44:04.490
Will we increase the amount
of suffering in the world?

00:44:04.490 --> 00:44:05.323
Should we do this?

00:44:05.323 --> 00:44:07.023
Under what conditions should we do this?

00:44:08.120 --> 00:44:11.470
- How does this work
affect whatever religious

00:44:11.470 --> 00:44:15.110
or spiritual values you hold, does it?

00:44:15.110 --> 00:44:16.340
- Yeah, of course, I think a lot about it.

00:44:16.340 --> 00:44:19.703
I was raised as a Roman Catholic
and I think a lot about it.

00:44:22.560 --> 00:44:24.060
To what extent is this,

00:44:24.060 --> 00:44:26.560
certainly it's difficult to reconcile some

00:44:26.560 --> 00:44:29.800
of these ideas with the
classical Roman Catholic doctrine

00:44:31.909 --> 00:44:34.700
of a freely independent actor.

00:44:34.700 --> 00:44:36.390
All right, this relates to the question

00:44:36.390 --> 00:44:37.223
we haven't talked about,

00:44:37.223 --> 00:44:39.320
to the question of free will and volition.

00:44:39.320 --> 00:44:41.520
But neuroscience, of
course, like all of science,

00:44:41.520 --> 00:44:43.810
throws some doubts on that,
some quote, water on the idea

00:44:43.810 --> 00:44:47.160
that I can really truly
act like the unmoved mover,

00:44:47.160 --> 00:44:48.620
the uncaused cause, right.

00:44:48.620 --> 00:44:51.820
Because how would that be if
I can truly act independent?

00:44:51.820 --> 00:44:54.480
That means that there's something happens

00:44:54.480 --> 00:44:56.640
without there being any
something happening before,

00:44:56.640 --> 00:45:00.170
and how's that supposed
to work in real life?

00:45:00.170 --> 00:45:02.387
So, those are issues I'm profoundly

00:45:02.387 --> 00:45:06.300
and passionately
interested in to reconcile,

00:45:06.300 --> 00:45:08.260
to come to a single
understanding of everything

00:45:08.260 --> 00:45:11.010
in the universe, including
things outside the universe.

00:45:12.940 --> 00:45:14.020
- Looking to the future,

00:45:14.020 --> 00:45:17.090
if you had to advise
students about how to prepare

00:45:17.090 --> 00:45:19.540
for the future in this field,

00:45:19.540 --> 00:45:21.420
what advice would you give them?

00:45:21.420 --> 00:45:24.210
I mean obviously they need to learn

00:45:24.210 --> 00:45:27.200
this array of scientific
skills that you require,

00:45:27.200 --> 00:45:32.200
but what about also humanistic
values and education

00:45:34.470 --> 00:45:36.450
with regard to dealing with this,

00:45:36.450 --> 00:45:38.663
once we come up with
some of these answers?

00:45:40.100 --> 00:45:41.260
- Well, I mean what I tell people

00:45:41.260 --> 00:45:44.210
who ask me what is they
want to do is study physics,

00:45:44.210 --> 00:45:48.300
study math, study biology,
study the basic sciences,

00:45:48.300 --> 00:45:51.280
be compassionate and leave
the world a better place.

00:45:51.280 --> 00:45:52.990
There really isn't much else to say.

00:45:52.990 --> 00:45:56.260
- (chuckles) And then finally,

00:45:56.260 --> 00:45:58.390
what about for the public,

00:45:58.390 --> 00:46:02.150
what is the best way to
follow this revolution?

00:46:02.150 --> 00:46:03.590
They're obviously not gonna go back

00:46:03.590 --> 00:46:05.810
and get graduate degrees, and so on,

00:46:05.810 --> 00:46:07.960
but do you have some
markers that people should--

00:46:07.960 --> 00:46:09.580
- [Christof] Well, they can read my book.

00:46:09.580 --> 00:46:12.990
- (laughs) yeah, yeah, right,
we'll show it again, right.

00:46:12.990 --> 00:46:14.280
- Well I mean there are now many journals,

00:46:14.280 --> 00:46:16.050
for example, Scientific
American just started

00:46:16.050 --> 00:46:18.476
a journal called Mind last year.

00:46:18.476 --> 00:46:20.840
Together with the normal
Scientific American,

00:46:20.840 --> 00:46:23.230
they have this second journal,
Scientific American Mind,

00:46:23.230 --> 00:46:26.840
that's just dedicated to
you know the dissemination

00:46:29.470 --> 00:46:30.910
of a lot of these ideas.

00:46:30.910 --> 00:46:33.480
So there are many books being
written, some very good books.

00:46:33.480 --> 00:46:36.277
John Searle has written
a wonderful little primer

00:46:36.277 --> 00:46:38.650
on consciousness and the mind.

00:46:38.650 --> 00:46:39.960
So, there are a number of excellent books

00:46:39.960 --> 00:46:41.530
that are now available
for the general public

00:46:41.530 --> 00:46:42.460
to inform themselves.

00:46:42.460 --> 00:46:46.230
The information's all there,
I mean they, it's not,

00:46:46.230 --> 00:46:47.810
you have to work at it.

00:46:47.810 --> 00:46:48.740
That's not surprising.

00:46:48.740 --> 00:46:50.840
Consciousness is a very puzzling thing

00:46:50.840 --> 00:46:52.200
and it you know can't be reduced

00:46:52.200 --> 00:46:54.650
to a single sound bite, right.

00:46:54.650 --> 00:46:55.990
I mean If you ask me what's consciousness

00:46:55.990 --> 00:46:56.823
in 30 seconds or less,

00:46:56.823 --> 00:46:58.319
you know it's difficult to answer that.

00:46:58.319 --> 00:47:00.327
But there are some
wonderful books available

00:47:00.327 --> 00:47:03.570
that describe the current
state of knowledge,

00:47:03.570 --> 00:47:07.530
incomplete as it is, for general public.

00:47:07.530 --> 00:47:11.493
- I'm curious, looking back at
the trajectory of your life,

00:47:12.870 --> 00:47:14.320
are there some certain factors

00:47:14.320 --> 00:47:18.820
that have brought you to
this focus in your life?

00:47:18.820 --> 00:47:21.940
I mean does it all come
together, in a way, in this,

00:47:21.940 --> 00:47:24.340
or is it primarily the science education

00:47:24.340 --> 00:47:25.603
that has led you here?

00:47:26.520 --> 00:47:28.073
- No, it's, well, I mean,

00:47:28.920 --> 00:47:30.660
life is always a series of accidents

00:47:30.660 --> 00:47:34.200
and then some more profound
current that tug you,

00:47:34.200 --> 00:47:36.130
that pull you along in
a certain direction.

00:47:36.130 --> 00:47:39.900
So I've always had, probably
because of the way my parents

00:47:39.900 --> 00:47:41.890
raised me in a very religious setting,

00:47:41.890 --> 00:47:43.730
always thought a lot about some

00:47:43.730 --> 00:47:45.440
of these more fundamental
problems about time,

00:47:45.440 --> 00:47:47.627
about eternity, about life before death,

00:47:47.627 --> 00:47:49.690
and life after death.

00:47:49.690 --> 00:47:50.660
But it's always puzzled me

00:47:50.660 --> 00:47:53.053
that people are much more
obsessed about life after death

00:47:53.053 --> 00:47:54.480
than life before death, right.

00:47:54.480 --> 00:47:55.313
Isn't it strange?

00:47:55.313 --> 00:47:56.520
People are really,

00:47:56.520 --> 00:47:57.970
particularly in the
context of consciousness.

00:47:57.970 --> 00:47:59.770
They rarely ask, well,

00:47:59.770 --> 00:48:02.920
what does it tell you
about life before birth?

00:48:02.920 --> 00:48:05.150
Where was I before I
came into this planet?

00:48:05.150 --> 00:48:06.210
They're always obsessed

00:48:06.210 --> 00:48:07.840
about what happens after they go out.

00:48:07.840 --> 00:48:12.480
Anyhow, no but, so that
certainly had a large influence,

00:48:12.480 --> 00:48:15.083
you know thinking about
these big problems,

00:48:16.320 --> 00:48:21.320
and I discovered, I learned
that the only way we can answer

00:48:21.400 --> 00:48:25.920
these problems in any satisfactory
way is by doing science.

00:48:25.920 --> 00:48:27.320
I mean, it's great to do philosophy,

00:48:27.320 --> 00:48:28.730
you can think about it,
everybody should do it,

00:48:28.730 --> 00:48:30.670
but ultimately you
can't prove any of that.

00:48:30.670 --> 00:48:34.910
And so the only sure
touchstone we have seems to me

00:48:34.910 --> 00:48:37.010
this empirical knowledge.

00:48:37.010 --> 00:48:39.980
The rest, we just have
to believe something.

00:48:39.980 --> 00:48:41.320
- Well, Christof, on that note,

00:48:41.320 --> 00:48:46.320
I wanna thank you for sharing
your intellectual odyssey,

00:48:47.000 --> 00:48:50.042
and also for being patient with us

00:48:50.042 --> 00:48:53.020
for trying to get into this,

00:48:53.020 --> 00:48:56.480
the complexity that you're working on.

00:48:56.480 --> 00:48:59.560
I wanna show the audience your book again,

00:48:59.560 --> 00:49:02.690
The Quest for Consciousness,
which I recommend highly.

00:49:02.690 --> 00:49:05.100
And I wanna thank you very
much for being here today.

00:49:05.100 --> 00:49:06.800
- Thank you very much,
Harry. It was a pleasure.

00:49:06.800 --> 00:49:09.130
- And thank you very much for joining us

